10 years today. Wow. 2022 was an exceptionally shitty year for me. However despite a nervous breakdown, my mother’s passing, the death of friends, the return of my epilepsy, Colonel Puff Puff’s cancer, money problems, I stayed sober. Believe, there were many times I wanted to check out or just disappear but I stayed. After 17 years of relapsing, it just feels surreal to have 10 years clean and sober.  I especially want to thank Jay Westbrook, @anouskadegeorgiou, @jeremythegirl, @joshiku & @lizziekeith for staying with me and walking me through a lot of hysteria & crying, some disassociation (can’t recommend that enough. Ugh.) and seizure activity.  And if you think you’ll never get it, please know I felt the same for so so long.  And thank you to all of you who remind me everyday I’m useful and valuable no matter what my head says. ❤️❤️❤️

I love you so much.❤️❤️❤️❤️ #goodfriends #10yearssober #carairfreshener #colonelpuffpuff

This is incredibly humbling and embarrassing but I need your help.  As you know my mom died in June.  My father is fighting for his life as we speak, having started chemo yesterday AGAIN.  Colonel Puff Puff has beat cancer for now but his kidney disease is out of control.  I'm waiting for my agent to shop the second book.  All of the stress has my epilepsy back and worse than ever. I'm titrating off very powerful medications and onto other medications. I am trying to freelance and do some things to make money but I can't think very clearly with all the seizure episodes and medications.  Plus I'm extremely tired and dizzy. I have very little income and tons of debt.  I have moved into a friend's guest house to save on rent.  I can't drive because of my epilepsy so I'm basically stuck and isolated and dependent.  I apologize for not posting on Patreon but my brain is not working properly.  We lost our big sponsor which is why the podcast has been down. As a lot of you know, I had a nervous breakdown last year and started to disassociate and then my mom died and yada yada. It's been some really rough sledding. I will be using the money to live and survive. Most of you know it's been a terribly rough year but it just keeps on getting worse.  I can't get on disability so I'm asking you for your help.  If my book helped you or I ever made you laugh or inspired you, please donate. I am still sober through all of this. #pleasehelp #gofundme 

Link in bio. Thanks. ❤️

My father is dying. After a month in the hospital where he lost 50 lbs, he has been moved to hospice. If you know me, you know my father is my everything: mentor, confidant, hero, person I love most in the world. There are no words to describe my grief and devastation. (This is not a current pic. I wouldn’t dishonor him or mess with his vanity.) He is a force of nature, bigger than life, the wittiest smartest person I’ve ever known and the best father I could have ever wished for. 💔I have no idea how I’ll continue on without him. #daddysgirls #fuckcancer #papaisdying 😭 I can only take solace in the fact that I made him proud. I am who I am because of him. Crying as I write this. The pain is unbearable but he said, “You are still unbreakable. Don’t let me change  that.” #unbreakable

I said goodbye to my papa last night, told him how much I loved him, assured him I would be okay but would miss him terribly and gave him permission to go. He couldn’t answer back but his whole face got peaceful. I predicted he would pass at 2:30 last night and that’s exactly when he died. I’m no psychic but our bond was insanely strong. I can’t believe I’ll never talk to him or touch him or see him again. I’m in shock. So glad he’s at peace now. Knowing he was in pain was destroying me. I love you papa. My heart is broken. Your words and lessons will live in me forever. You were so special. #ripdad #fuckcancer #unbreakable

I had to let my beautiful Colonel Puff Puff go today. His kidney failure was causing him to suffer and I made the extremely hard but loving choice to stop that suffering and protect him from more suffering. He was the weirdest bravest most affectionate cat I’ve ever had. “I love you more than words can express and you are already missed, Colonel. Thank you for walking me through some of the hardest six years of my life.” My heart is broken. My eyes are swollen from tears. The house feels eerily empty. And tonight  will be so lonely without him tucked under my arm. Tomorrow I fly up to deal with my father’s affairs.  It’s my season of grief I guess. #rip #colonelpuffpuff #byemykitty #fuckkidneydisease #seasonofgrief 😭💔😿
#griefsucks #missyouguys #sadness #loneliness #restinpeace

Happy Birthday Papa. My dad would have been 86 today if cancer hadn't taken him on March 17th. I know 86 sounds old but he was still the smartest, funniest, wittiest person I knew. He was also my rock and my best friend. The grief of losing him is still staggeringly painful and I feel a bit lost without our daily calls. We wrote each poems for each other's birthdays for as long as I can remember. Maybe I will write him a poem today and read it and burn it. 

Today I celebrate you, Papa. Thank you for teaching me to write, play poker, ride a bike, swim, tell terrible jokes and love.

I miss and love you more than you'll ever know. My heart is still broken by your passing but I will persevere because, as you said on your deathbed, I'm your “legacy.” #rippapa #mydaddysbirthday #griefandloss #imissmydad #fuckcancer #myrockisgone

I’m sprinkling my dad’s ashes today at the beach. Father’s Day was a little tough this year but I tried to stay busy. 

This is my father’s star sapphire ring that had been my grandfather’s. My father wore it after my grandfather died and now I will wear it since my father has died. We polished it (hadn’t been polished in over 100 years for sure) and set in a more feminine setting.  I used to play with it on my grandfather’s finger when I was a little girl, sitting on his lap in the Miami sun. I remember my father wearing it in the hospital as I held his hand, weeks before he passed. 

To me it looks and feels magical. When I put it on yesterday I felt a peace, like my papa was with me. It twinkles and flashes just like his eyes. I love and miss you papa. I hope today brings me some closure but I don’t think you ever get full closure when a parent dies. 

#familyheirloom #starsapphire #mydaddysring😢 #missyoudad 

Thank you @goldandgemsfinejewelry for the  beautiful work on this ring that means the world to me. Ron you are the best!

Proof of life. 🤣🤣 No I’m not stoned. I’ve just been crying every day for months. Sprinkled my mom’s ashes last night on a mountain. Wept and then saw a large beautiful pink moon. Only Colonel’s ashes are left now. I’m slowly putting myself back together after this hurricane of grief. Apologies for not posting much. Just don’t have a lot to say at the moment. Still processing. No eyelash extensions until the crying stops. Those fuckers are too expensive. But I am here & sober and getting through, not gracefully but who cares. ❤️‍🩹🤘🏼⛅️

Between the losses of my mother, father and Colonel Puff Puff, the constant subclinical seizure activity and the horrible side effects of the newest anti-convulsant medication, I ended up checking myself into Las Encinas for suicidal ideation last Wednesday. I was discharged on Monday. Did they fix me? No. Did they keep me safe until the ideation passed? Yes. Was the food good? No. Did it remind me of the power of connection? Yes. 

I laughed. I made two bead bracelets. I crushed out on a male nurse. I actually cried when I left because I felt safe there. I’m far from where I need to be but I remembered who I can be. 

I’m having Vagus Nerve Stimulator surgery sometime in the next couple of months so that I can get off this awful seizure medication. Hopefully that will allow me to think clearly and drive again. I feel inspired to write for the first time in months. 

Mental health is still so stigmatized. At 10.5 years sober, I did not think I’d be back in the psych ward. But the medication can cause suicidal ideation and honestly, it all just felt like too much to carry. I’m alive and sober and goddamn if this isn’t good material. Sure, that’s the writer in me trying to make something good of something horrible and create a defense against the shame.

This is all to say fuck the stigma. I want people to know they're not alone. I don't care if this "doesn't look good". This is real life. 80% of people with substance use disorder have mental health issues. Let’s talk about it. And for the love of God, if you’re feeling suicidal, open your mouth and get help. #epilepsy #grief #loss #suicidalideation #psychhospital #medication #fuckshame #fuckthestigma #mentalillness #mentalhealth #sobriety

Thank you @anthonyvenegasdesign for making this for me. What’s so spooky is that you never read my book so you didn’t know my dad said, “My friends wish they had a kid as unbreakable as you”. I’ll take it as a sign from my papa to keep going. Sometimes it’s the little things that matter. ❤️ #signsfromtheotherside #unbreakable #youareabeast #keepgoing #myfairjunkie #mypapa 

P.S. And right before he died he said, “You’re still unbreakable. Don’t let me change that”. 🥲🙏💕

Well I'm officially bionic. 

Last Thursday I had VNS surgery to try to control my epilepsy.  They make an incision in your chest, slide in a battery and then snake a wire up your vagus nerve about midway up your neck.  That's where the second incision is. I won't post post-surgery pics because they're pretty gnarly and I was told to "try to be normal" by a friend so this is my attempt to do so. ;) 

Today I went to the neurologist to have the device turned on.  They start you at a very low frequency.  In 2 weeks, she will turn it up. Every few minutes, a burst of electricity goes up your vagus nerve into your brain. If you feel a seizure coming on, you can swipe a magnet across the battery and give yourself an extra boost.  Off label it can help with depression.

So my doctor turns it on and after a few minutes asks how I feel. 

I tell her that I feel a tickle in my throat (where the wire stops) and that I feel nervous but more awake and I show her a trembling hand. I tell her my feet are tingling. 

She then says to me, "Let's turn it off for 10 minutes and see if you feel better."

Ten minutes later she comes in and says, "How do you feel?"

"Much calmer, "I said. "But I feel tired now. Look I'm not shaking any more," and I put out a steady hand.

"I never turned it off," she says. 

I start laughing maniacally.  The nurse smiles. They show me the note I'm showing you here.

"I'm not trying to make you feel bad. I'm just trying to show you that it's in your head.  You're just nervous and that's understandable!  Nobody wants a pacemaker for their brain in their chest."

Never ever forget how powerful your mind and beliefs are. 

#vns #vnstherapy 
#vagusnervestimulator #neurologist #epilepsy #bionic #lovemydoctor #mindispowerful

In a year where there was been a lot of loss, grief, change and generally scary shit, I'm incredibly honored and excited to have landed with @ultraliterary 

I'm trashing the old proposal, starting totally fresh with a new idea, new take and new representation. I'm posting this to make MYSELF accountable to get on with the proposal.

 If I've learned anything in the last year, it's that those old sayings "let go or be dragged" and "it's only after you jump that the net appears" are unfortunately true. Terrifying. But hey I didn't make the rules. 

Thank you for your continued support of my first book and I sincerely hope you will support and love the second. Apologies it's taken awhile but everybody died and then I lost my mind and then I became bionic so.... 
#freshstart #myfairjunkie #painintoart #newagent #betterlatethannever #letsdothis #writerslife

I have 11 years in recovery today. Very grateful and kind of shocked to be honest. This past year was the most difficult of my life, let alone of my sobriety. There were so many moments I wanted to escape my feelings, check out in any way possible, temporarily and permanently. But I didn't. And that's what matters. Not how I felt but what I DID.  I now know I can stay sober through the most brutal of losses, the most terrifying of what life can dish out. Still here and ready to write the next chapter, literally and figuratively. I'm incredibly thankful to my friends who have, at times, literally, carried me. You know who you are. And thanks to you who have sent or posted messages of concern and support or just even thought them. I felt it. Love you all. #unbreakable #11years #soberanniversary #stillhere
